    // getters and setters
}
```

2. Then, create a DAO (data access object) interface that defines the methods to interact with the database. For example:

```java
@Dao
public interface BookDao {
    @Query("SELECT * FROM books")
    List<Book> getAll();

    @Insert
    void insertAll(List<Book> books);
}
```

3. Create a Room database that includes your entity (Book) and DAO (BookDao). For example:

```java
@Database(entities = {Book.class}, version = 1, exportSchema = false)
